The paper deals with the security issue of distributed storage systems, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also considers the clustered nature of distributed storage systems, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). The eavesdropper models and network coding scheme proposed in the paper involve communication networks (cs.NI) and information security (cs.SI).
